# 04. What command gives you the time since your system was last booted?(BLUE)

uptime

# the command uptime tells how long the system has been running.
# it gives one line display of the following information.
# 17:40:30 up 4 min, 1 user, load average: 0.05, 0.23, 0.12
# current time -> how long the system has been running -> how many
# users are currently logged on -> the system load average for the 
# past 1, 5 and 15 minutes.
